<br>
Standing in snow up to her knees, the young gnome glared at Alleusion. The ground shook with the force of the steps from a nearby shardwurm, turning the small wizard's glare into one of alarm. With a slight turn of her wrist, the enchanter vanished. Amusement lit her eyes as she watched her young friend fumble through her spellbook. Standing, shivering violently, Cablatinu tried to channel her thoughts into her invisibility spell, failing once, then twice.<br>
<br>
Growing increasingly nervous at the nearing steps of the wurm, Cablatinu turned her frustrations on to her friend. &quot;Json thon wikb, nuy json you Alleusion ior dhaggyer mk meee.&quot;<br>
<br>
Shedding her veil of invisibility, Alleusion turned to her companion, &quot;He ic sqqug mf friin. I am sorry my friend. Seshaps nhor hilq help. Perhaps this will help.&quot; Speaking in both the native tongue of the gnomes and the crude common tongue, Alleusion began the long cast of the calming spell her Koa'dal ancestors had passed down from long ago - Koadic's Endless Intellect.<br>
<br>
Vanishing once again, patiently waiting for the wizard to do the same, Alleusion turned to the wind. Even though the high elf did not posess the skill of the tracker, she knew she was headed in the right direction.<br>
<br>
Head bent, using her withered staff for support, the enchanter pushed through the wall of wind. It was almost as if the winf knew her destination and would do whatever it took to keep her away. With her destination in sight along with the stout Coldain dwarves, Alleusion let her thoughts wander.<br>
<br>
Absentmindedly, the tall, pale high elf took a piece of parchment from a dwarf that had come rushing up to her. Ignoring it and reaching into her robes, her fingers fluttered over a well worn piece of paper, the words burned into her mind.<br>
<br>
     Sister, I've left for Thurgadin. My quest for my prayer shawlis nearing completion. You have always watched over me, possibly too closely. I need to do this on my own. Do not follow me.<br>
                                   Caony<br>
<br>
Hot, unshed tears burned behind her eyes. Her heart begged for their release, but her pride would not allow them to fall. It felt like yesterday that the squalling baby had been thrust into her hands. Images raced in her mind...the toddler taking her first steps...the joy in her eyes when she learned the gift of healing...the frustration...the anger, and finally the sadness that drove Caony away.<br>
<br>
Cablatinu glanced at Alleusion as she watched her friend open the letter the dwarf had given her. Then she openly stared in shock as she watched the calm face of the enchanter she had come to love turn into one twisted with a mixture of pain and rage. Clutched in her hand, knuckles white with force, was the crumpled letter...forgotten. A single whisper, followed by a single tear, followed by a shout of fury that caused even the far away giants to pause, ripped through the wind and across the hills.<br>
<br>
&quot;CAONY!!&quot;<br>
<br>
Letting the parchment fal to the snow, Alleusion turned and stalked into the Coldain city. Still in shock, the small gnome stared as her friend vanished into the velium waterfall. Bending, with shaking fingers, she reached for the paper. Fear widening her eyes, she read the clumsy script of the Kromriff Giants.<br>
